'''The Pine Creek Wilderness''' is a  natural environment designated by United States Congress in 1984.<ref name="CaliforniaTrailMap">{{cite web|title=Pine Creek Wilderness - U.S. Forest Service - Wilderness|url=http://www.californiatrailmap.com/TrailFinder/Pine-Creek-Wilderness/|website=CaliforniaTrailMap.com|publisher=CaliforniaTrailMap|accessdate=14 January 2018}}</ref> It is located entirely in California, and managed by [[United States Forest Service]].<ref name="Wilderness.net">{{cite web|title=Pine Creek Wilderness|url=http://www.wilderness.net/NWPS/wildView?WID=457|website=Wilderness.net|publisher=Wilderness.net|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>

==General==
The Pine Creek Wilderness is sloping area in the Cleveland National Forest, spread across an area of 13,261 acres. It is ranging from 2,000 feet elevation in the south to 4,000 feet in the north. It is situated entirely in [[California]], bordered by the Hauser Wilderness to the south.<ref name="Wilderness.net" />

