'''Rynersonite''' ([[calcium|Ca]]([[tantalum|Ta]],[[niobium|Nb]])<sub>2</sub>[[oxygen|O]]<sub>6</sub>) is an oxide [[mineral]]. It crystallizes in the [[orthorhombic]] [[crystal system]]. It is dull, translucent mineral, fibrous in nature. Usually off-white to pale pink in color. It occurs in [[granite|granitic]] [[pegmatite]]s and was first described for an occurrence in [[San Diego County, California]] in 1978.<ref>http://www.webmineral.com/data/Rynersonite.shtml Webmineral</ref><ref>http://www.mindat.org/min-3488.html Mindat.org</ref><ref>[http://www.handbookofmineralogy.com/pdfs/rynersonite.pdf Handbook of Mineralogy - Rynersonite]</ref>
Besides the San Diego, California area, Rynersonite is also found in [[Colorado]] and [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]].
