'''South Atlantic High''' is a semipermanent [[anticyclone|pressure high]] centered at about [[latitude|25°S]], [[longitude|15°W]], in the [[Atlantic Ocean]]. It is also called the '''St. Helena High'''. It can stretch thousands of miles across the South Atlantic.

