{{italic title}}
'''''The Emperor Lays an Egg''''' is a non-fiction children's picture book by Brenda Z. Guiberson, with pictures by Joan Paley.<ref>[http://b186625.booqster.com/ ''The Emperor Lays an Egg'' at Booqster]</ref> 

==Summary==
An [[emperor penguin]] father has to protect his [[egg (biology)|egg]] for two months while the mother is off searching for food. The book has information about the [[birth]] cycle of emperor penguins and it has a story of a mother and father caring for their egg.

==Reception==
*A ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'' review says, "Although The Emperor's Egg, by Martin Jenkins (1999), covers similar territory, school and public libraries will find this title useful for elementary school science reports, and nature lovers will love the pictures".<ref>[http://www.allbusiness.com/retail-trade/miscellaneous-retail-miscellaneous/4776523-1.html ''Kirkus Reviews'' November 1, 2001]</ref>
*It was reviewed by ''[[Booklist]]''.<ref>[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-27216905_ITM Booklist December 1, 2001]</ref> and ''[[Horn Book Magazine]]''.<ref>[http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-82322616.html ''Horn Book Magazine'' January 1, 2002]</ref>

